<paragraph id="F92336D0FFBA590D5B3AC959B3BCF988" blockId="12.[818,1327,1578,1635]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading id="A26B81BCFFBA590D5B3AC959B3BCF988" bold="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5B3AC959B4F0F9A8" bold="true" box="[818,1195,1578,1603]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5B3AC959B381F9A8" authority="Boppré &amp; Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Monzón, 2020" authorityName="Boppré &amp; Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Monzón" authorityYear="2020" box="[818,986,1578,1603]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Vanewrightia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5B3AC959B381F9A8" bold="true" box="[818,986,1578,1603]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Vanewrightia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D0DB57B9FFBA590D5BE9C959B40AF9A8" box="[993,1105,1578,1603]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
versus
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5CBBC959B3BCF988" authority="Hubner, [1819]" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5CBBC959B3BCF988" bold="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5CBBC959B574F9A8" bold="true" box="[1203,1327,1578,1603]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Epidesma</emphasis>
Hübner, [1819]
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F92336D0FFBA590D5B3AC905B560F92E" blockId="12.[818,1442,1654,1938]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Establishing 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5BAEC905B47AF961" authorityName="Boppré &amp; Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Monzón" authorityYear="2020" box="[934,1057,1654,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Vanewrightia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5BAEC905B47AF961" box="[934,1057,1654,1674]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Vanewrightia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not resolve 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5CB7C905B542F961" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1215,1305,1654,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5CB7C905B542F961" box="[1215,1305,1654,1674]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appearing as a polyphyletic genus like many other genera in the current taxonomy of Arctiinae; 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5BA2C9C2B45FF92E" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[938,1028,1713,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5BA2C9C2B45FF92E" box="[938,1028,1713,1733]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in need of a thorough revision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B186655BFFBA590E5B5AC9BDB243FEEB" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="F92336D0FFBA590F5B5AC9BDB126F999" blockId="12.[818,1442,1654,1938]" lastBlockId="14.[146,771,1571,1943]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
A common denominator of all 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5C8FC9BDB4BAF909" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1159,1249,1742,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5C8FC9BDB4BAF909" box="[1159,1249,1742,1762]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an oblique forewing band, a character that 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5C5AC99FB4F7F8EB" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[1106,1196,1772,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5C5AC99FB4F7F8EB" box="[1106,1196,1772,1792]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares with many other moths and butterflies (see Discussion). Having found highly variable taxa (see above) and realizing that the currently recognized species of 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5B9FC837B3AAF8B3" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[919,1009,1860,1880]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5B9FC837B3AAF8B3" box="[919,1009,1860,1880]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar in appearance renders their status doubtful. Because the full range of pattern variation is not yet known (in 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5BC9C80CB441F879" authorityName="Boppré &amp; Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Monzón" authorityYear="2020" box="[961,1050,1918,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Vanewrightia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiesela">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5BC9C80CB441F879" box="[961,1050,1918,1938]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">V. kiesela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBA590D5C46C80CB489F879" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1102,1234,1918,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurimacula">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBA590D5C46C80CB489F879" box="[1102,1234,1918,1938]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">E. aurimacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, perhaps, further 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F589AC950B0B7F9DC" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[146,236,1571,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F589AC950B0B7F9DC" box="[146,236,1571,1591]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), only with large series of specimens, of which genitalia and DNA sequences are available, can the long-outstanding revision of 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F58A3C92DB15EF999" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[171,261,1630,1650]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F58A3C92DB15EF999" box="[171,261,1630,1650]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
be achieved.
</paragraph>
<caption id="ADE36658FFBB590C589AC98AB546F8BD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384277" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5384277" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384277/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" startId="13.[146,172,1785,1802]" targetBox="[186,1409,158,1748]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="F92336D0FFBB590C589AC98AB546F8BD" blockId="13.[146,1442,1785,1878]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C589AC98AB091F8E1" bold="true" box="[146,202,1785,1802]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig.12.</emphasis>
Selection of species of 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C598DC98AB18EF8E1" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[389,469,1785,1802]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C598DC98AB18EF8E1" box="[389,469,1785,1802]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to demonstrate their variation and similarity with respect to wing pattern versus male genitalia.(A‒F) 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C5CFDC98AB5F9F8E1" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1269,1442,1785,1802]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurimacula" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5CFDC98AB5F9F8E1" box="[1269,1442,1785,1802]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Epidesma aurimacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D0DB57B9FFBB590C589AC860B087F8CF" box="[146,220,1811,1828]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from Panguana/Peru (A, B), from French Guiana (C, D), from Bolivia (E), from Venezuela (F). (G) 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C5BE9C860B475F8CF" baseAuthorityName="Rothschild" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[993,1070,1811,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Oridishia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klagesi">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5BE9C860B475F8CF" box="[993,1070,1811,1828]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. klagesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (H) 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C5C5CC860B4C0F8CF" baseAuthorityName="Hering" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[1108,1179,1811,1828]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Erbessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursula">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5C5CC860B4C0F8CF" box="[1108,1179,1811,1828]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. ursula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from French Guiana. (I) 
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5D57C860B532F8CF" box="[1375,1385,1811,1828]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E</emphasis>
. sp. nr 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C589AC85FB09EF8D6" baseAuthorityName="Hering" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[146,197,1836,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Erbessa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursula">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C589AC85FB09EF8D6" box="[146,197,1836,1853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">ursula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Costa Rica.(K) 
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5961C85FB128F8D6" box="[361,371,1836,1853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E</emphasis>
. sp.nr 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C59A5C85FB1BEF8D6" baseAuthorityName="Rothschild" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[429,485,1836,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Oridishia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klagesi">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C59A5C85FB1BEF8D6" box="[429,485,1836,1853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">klagesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Costa Rica.(L) 
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5A80C85FB2C9F8D6" box="[648,658,1836,1853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E</emphasis>
. nr 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C5AB8C85FB2B5F8D6" authorityName="Travassos" authorityYear="1938" box="[688,750,1836,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crameri">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5AB8C85FB2B5F8D6" box="[688,750,1836,1853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">crameri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Peru.(M) Recently transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C5C30C85FB55CF8D6" authority="(Laguerre 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Laguerre" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[1080,1287,1836,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5C30C85FB4D3F8D6" box="[1080,1160,1836,1853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Epidesma</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9D0D4B21FFBB590C5C99C85FB55BF8D6" author="Laguerre, M." box="[1169,1280,1836,1853]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="47 - 56" refId="ref14758" refString="Laguerre, M. 2019. Description of two new genera and four new species of Arctiinae from the Neotropical fauna (Lepidoptera: Erebidae: Arctiinae). Antenor 6: 47 - 56." type="journal article" year="2019">Laguerre 2019</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFBB590C5D06C85FB5C6F8D6" baseAuthorityName="Rothschild" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1294,1437,1836,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Aphymolis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFBB590C5D06C85FB5C6F8D6" box="[1294,1437,1836,1853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Aphymolis similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; left upperside,right underside;genitalia dorsal,ventral,phallus from left to right. Scale bars = 1 cm for moths,1 mm for genitalia. See also Fig. 4.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="ADE36658FFB8590F589BCAC0B3A6FA1D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384279" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5384279" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384279/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" startId="14.[147,174,1459,1476]" targetBox="[147,1442,151,1423]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph id="F92336D0FFB8590F589BCAC0B3A6FA1D" blockId="14.[146,1444,1459,1526]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F589BCAC0B095FA2F" bold="true" box="[147,206,1459,1476]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 13.</emphasis>
Neighbor-joining distance tree of 27 COI sequences of 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5A84CAC0B2A3FA2F" authority="Boppré &amp; Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Monzón, 2020" authorityName="Boppré &amp; Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Monzón" authorityYear="2020" box="[652,760,1459,1476]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Vanewrightia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen.nov.">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5A84CAC0B2A3FA2F" box="[652,760,1459,1476]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Vanewrightia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D0DB57B9FFB8590F5AF4CAC0B313FA2F" box="[764,840,1459,1476]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="genus">gen.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 38 of its neighbors from BOLDSYSTEMS (2019) with BIN BOLD codes. Distances (normalized to 1) are given below each branch (omitted if &lt;0.002) and bootstrap supports above each branch (in bold, only if&gt;70%) obtained with MEGA7 (
<bibRefCitation id="9D0D4B21FFB8590F58D2CA96B13CFA1D" author="Kumar, S. &amp; G. Stecher &amp; K. Tamura" box="[218,359,1509,1526]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1870 - 1874" refId="ref14669" refString="Kumar, S., G. Stecher, and K. Tamura. 2016. MEGA 7: molecular evolutionary genetics analysis version 7.0 for bigger datasets. Mol. Biol. Evol. 33: 1870 - 1874." type="journal article" year="2016">Kumar et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
