<paragraph id="F92336D0FFB8590F58BAC908B3E6F947" blockId="14.[146,771,1571,1943]" lastBlockId="14.[818,1443,1571,1943]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The BOLD database (
<bibRefCitation id="9D0D4B21FFB8590F598DC908B20CF964" author="BOLDSYSTEMS" box="[389,599,1659,1679]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref13546" refString="BOLDSYSTEMS. 2020. Barcode of life data system. (http: // v 4. boldsystems. org /) (accessed 22 May 2020)." type="url" year="2020">BOLDSYSTEMS 2020</bibRefCitation>
) currently houses sequences of 
<specimenCount id="EF9AFD59FFB8590F591AC9EBB1C7F947" box="[274,412,1688,1708]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="generic">230 specimens</specimenCount>
(167 from 
<collectingCountry id="818B7640FFB8590F5A19C9EBB220F947" box="[529,635,1688,1708]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
) of 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5AA0C9EBB359F947" baseAuthorityName="Laguerre" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[680,770,1688,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5AA0C9EBB359F947" box="[680,770,1688,1708]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given 42 names; only six BINs are public which include seven names. FUNET (
<bibRefCitation id="9D0D4B21FFB8590F58EFC9A0B10CF90C" author="Savela, M." box="[231,343,1747,1767]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref15447" refString="Savela, M. 2020. Lepidoptera and some other life forms. Online Database. (http: // www. nic. funet. fi / pub / sci / bio / life / insecta / lepidoptera /) (accessed 14 May 2020)." type="url" year="2020">Savela 2020</bibRefCitation>
) currently recognizes 15 species of which two have to be omitted (
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5942C982B1C5F8EF" baseAuthorityName="Rothschild" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[330,414,1776,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Aphymolis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5942C982B1C5F8EF" box="[330,414,1776,1796]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is now in 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F59F6C983B359F8EF" authority="(Laguerre, 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Laguerre" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[510,770,1776,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Aphymolis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F59F6C983B23AF8EF" box="[510,609,1776,1796]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Aphymolis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9D0D4B21FFB8590F5A66C982B2A1F8EF" author="Laguerre, M." box="[622,762,1776,1796]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="47 - 56" refId="ref14758" refString="Laguerre, M. 2019. Description of two new genera and four new species of Arctiinae from the Neotropical fauna (Lepidoptera: Erebidae: Arctiinae). Antenor 6: 47 - 56." type="journal article" year="2019">Laguerre, 2019</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F58B4C87CB0ABF8CA" baseAuthorityName="Rothschild" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[188,240,1807,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parva">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F58B4C87CB0ABF8CA" box="[188,240,1807,1825]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">parva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= 
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5903C87DB12BF8C9" box="[267,368,1806,1826]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">albimacula</emphasis>
, see above). The name of the 
<typeStatus id="26278872FFB8590F5A87C87CB2EDF8C9" box="[655,694,1807,1826]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F589AC858B1E0F8D4" authority="(Stoll, [1781])" baseAuthorityName="Stoll" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[146,443,1835,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursula">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F589AC858B175F8D4" box="[146,302,1835,1855]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Epidesma ursula</emphasis>
(Stoll, [1781])
</taxonomicName>
, appears in three BINs, but likely none represents 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5921C83AB126F8B7" baseAuthorityName="Stoll" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[297,381,1864,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursula">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5921C83AB126F8B7" box="[297,381,1864,1884]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. ursula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D0DB57B9FFB8590F598CC83AB1F5F8B7" box="[388,430,1865,1884]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Notably, there is no new species description in this genus for the past 90 yr. The old descriptions were made quite superficially, all species greatly resemble each other, and only 
<bibRefCitation id="9D0D4B21FFB8590F5B57C957B3A7F9DC" author="Travassos, L." box="[863,1020,1571,1591]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref15871" refString="Travassos, L. 1938. Contribuicao ao conhecimento dos Euchromiidae: I. Genero Desmotricha Hampson, 1911 (Lepidoptera). Mem. Inst. Oswaldo Cruz 33: 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1938">Travassos (1938)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="9D0D4B21FFB8590F5C22C950B4FFF9DC" author="Cerda, J. - M." box="[1066,1188,1571,1591]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref13792" refString="Cerda, J. - M. 2017. Ctenuchina de Guyane francaise Lepidoptera, Erebidae, Arctiinae, Arctiini (partie 1). Memoires de la Societe linneenne de Lyon 7. 181 pp + 20 plates." type="book" year="2017">Cerda (2017)</bibRefCitation>
provided drawings of genitalia (of 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5B8BC932B383F9BF" baseAuthorityName="Stoll" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[899,984,1600,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ursula">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5B8BC932B383F9BF" box="[899,984,1600,1620]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. ursula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5BECC932B464F9BF" baseAuthorityName="Rothschild" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[996,1087,1600,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" genus="Oridishia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klagesi">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5BECC932B464F9BF" box="[996,1087,1600,1620]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. klagesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5C43C932B495F9BF" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1099,1230,1600,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurimacula">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5C43C932B495F9BF" box="[1099,1230,1600,1620]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. aurimacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5D0DC932B53DF9B8" authorityName="Travassos" authorityYear="1938" box="[1285,1382,1601,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crameri">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5D0DC932B53DF9B8" box="[1285,1382,1601,1619]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. crameri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only). 
<figureCitation id="61A72A55FFB8590F5B3AC92DB3D6F999" box="[818,909,1630,1650]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[146,172,1785,1802]" captionTargetBox="[186,1409,158,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-2@13.[171,1417,147,1750]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig.12. Selection of species of Epidesmato demonstrate their variation and similarity with respect to wing pattern versus male genitalia.(A‒F) Epidesma aurimacula syn. nov. from Panguana/Peru (A, B), from French Guiana (C, D), from Bolivia (E), from Venezuela (F). (G) E. klagesi. (H) E. ursula from French Guiana. (I) E. sp. nr ursula from Costa Rica.(K) E. sp.nr klagesi from Costa Rica.(L) E. nr crameri from Peru.(M) Recently transferred from Epidesma (Laguerre 2019): Aphymolis similis; left upperside,right underside;genitalia dorsal,ventral,phallus from left to right. Scale bars = 1 cm for moths,1 mm for genitalia. See also Fig. 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384277" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384277/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figure 12</figureCitation>
documents the variation and similarity with respect to wing pattern versus male genitalia for some species of 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5D40C908B5F9F964" baseAuthorityName="Laguerre" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[1352,1442,1659,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5D40C908B5F9F964" box="[1352,1442,1659,1679]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
available to us.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F92336D0FFB8590E5B5AC9C4B243FEEB" blockId="14.[818,1443,1571,1943]" lastBlockId="15.[146,770,148,256]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
In conclusion, the polyphyly of 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5C72C9C5B48FF921" baseAuthorityName="Laguerre" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[1146,1236,1718,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5C72C9C5B48FF921" box="[1146,1236,1718,1738]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be resolved at present. In particular, the knowledge on variation in 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5D2FC9A0B5F9F90C" authorityName="Boppré &amp; Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Monzón" authorityYear="2020" box="[1319,1442,1747,1767]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Vanewrightia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5D2FC9A0B5F9F90C" box="[1319,1442,1747,1767]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Vanewrightia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5B54C982B3BBF8EF" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[860,992,1776,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurimacula">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5B54C982B3BBF8EF" box="[860,992,1776,1796]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. aurimacula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
documented here makes it likely that there are further species with more or less intraspecific variation and questions if all currently recognized species are valid. To provide meaningful characters to delimit species morphologically (and eventually for characterizing genera), genitalia and barcodes of many specimens from many localities are required for both 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB8590F5CF5C8F0B523F87C" authorityName="Boppré &amp; Grados &amp; Laguerre &amp; Monzón" authorityYear="2020" box="[1277,1400,1923,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Vanewrightia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB8590F5CF5C8F0B523F87C" box="[1277,1400,1923,1943]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Vanewrightia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and all 
<taxonomicName id="3E9C4D53FFB9590E58A5CFE7B15CFF43" baseAuthorityName="Laguerre" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[173,263,148,168]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epidesma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBE8EAC2FFB9590E58A5CFE7B15CFF43" box="[173,263,148,168]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Epidesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While this is a demanding prospect, it is now clear that the ‘ctenuchines with an oblique forewing band’ are not only taxonomically challenging but also very interesting, even more so when considering ecological aspects (see below).
</paragraph>
